A man in Njabini town, Kinangop was killed on Tuesday night and his body dumped near one of the rivers in the area. The deceased who was employed in a carwash was last seen in the company of his friends heading home in the evening before his body was found near the Midlands company. Kinangop OCPD Jane Munywoki confirmed the incident saying it was a case of outright murder and was being investigated. “Since he is well known in this area we have opened an inquest file and we call on anyone with information regarding the incident to volunteer it to the police,” she said. Meanwhile, police in Naivasha are closing in on a retired Chief who stabbed his friend to death following a quarrel in one of the clubs in the lakeside town. Click here for the latest political news.